{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1793,"text":"So, people are more afraid of insects\nthan they are of dying."},{"time":6809,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":8611,"text":"At least, according to a 1973\n\"Book of Lists\" survey"},{"time":13143,"text":"which preceded all those online best,\nworst, funniest lists that you see today."},{"time":20167,"text":"Only heights and public speaking"},{"time":23829,"text":"exceeded the six-legged\nas sources of fear."},{"time":27884,"text":"And I suspect if you had put\nspiders in there,"},{"time":31460,"text":"the combinations of insects and spiders\nwould have just topped the chart."},{"time":36736,"text":"Now, I am not one of those people."},{"time":38863,"text":"I really love insects."},{"time":41033,"text":"I think they're interesting and beautiful,"},{"time":45108,"text":"and sometimes even cute."},{"time":46620,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":48111,"text":"And I'm not alone."},{"time":49503,"text":"For centuries, some\nof the greatest minds in science,"},{"time":53233,"text":"from Charles Darwin to E.O. Wilson,"},{"time":56269,"text":"have drawn inspiration from studying\nsome of the smallest minds on Earth."},{"time":62661,"text":"Well, why is that?"},{"time":64386,"text":"What is that keeps us\ncoming back to insects?"},{"time":68055,"text":"Some of it, of course, is just the sheer\nmagnitude of almost everything about them."},{"time":72678,"text":"They're more numerous\nthan any other kind of animal."},{"time":75689,"text":"We don't even know how many species\nof insects there are,"},{"time":78537,"text":"because new ones\nare being discovered all the time."},{"time":81278,"text":"There are at least a million,\nmaybe as many as 10 million."},{"time":85221,"text":"This means that you could have\nan insect-of-the-month calendar"},{"time":89509,"text":"and not have to reuse a species\nfor over 80,000 years."},{"time":93518,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":96442,"text":"Take that, pandas and kittens!"},{"time":98154,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":100506,"text":"More seriously, insects are essential."},{"time":103998,"text":"We need them."},{"time":105469,"text":"It's been estimated\nthat 1 out of every 3 bites of food"},{"time":108893,"text":"is made possible by a pollinator."},{"time":112972,"text":"Scientist use insects to make fundamental\ndiscoveries"},{"time":116223,"text":"about everything from the structure\nof our nervous systems"},{"time":119148,"text":"to how our genes and DNA work."},{"time":122388,"text":"But what I love most about insects"},{"time":124290,"text":"is what they can tell us\nabout our own behavior."},{"time":127539,"text":"Insects seem like they do\neverything that people do."},{"time":130620,"text":"They meet, they mate,\nthey fight, they break up."},{"time":134509,"text":"And they do so with what looks\nlike love or animosity."},{"time":139665,"text":"But what drives their behaviors is really\ndifferent than what drives our own,"},{"time":144900,"text":"and that difference\ncan be really illuminating."},{"time":148234,"text":"There's nowhere where that's more true"},{"time":150125,"text":"than when it comes to one\nof our most consuming interests -- sex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154142,"text":"Now, I will maintain.\nand I think I can defend,"},{"time":156999,"text":"what may seem like a surprising statement."},{"time":160749,"text":"I think sex in insects is more\ninteresting than sex in people."},{"time":164320,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":166131,"text":"And the wild variety that we see"},{"time":169294,"text":"makes us challenge\nsome of our own assumptions"},{"time":172231,"text":"about what it means to be male and female."},{"time":175663,"text":"Of course, to start with,"},{"time":177338,"text":"a lot of insects don't need\nto have sex at all to reproduce."},{"time":180319,"text":"Female aphids can make little, tiny clones\nof themselves without ever mating."},{"time":185441,"text":"Virgin birth, right there."},{"time":186938,"text":"On your rose bushes."},{"time":188250,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":191470,"text":"When they do have sex,"},{"time":193035,"text":"even their sperm is more\ninteresting than human sperm."},{"time":196316,"text":"There are some kinds of fruit flies"},{"time":198715,"text":"whose sperm is longer\nthan the male's own body."},{"time":202216,"text":"And that's important because the males\nuse their sperm to compete."},{"time":206873,"text":"Now, male insects do compete with weapons,\nlike the horns on these beetles."},{"time":211553,"text":"But they also compete\nafter mating with their sperm."},{"time":216726,"text":"Dragonflies and damselflies have penises\nthat look kind of like Swiss Army knives"},{"time":221876,"text":"with all of the attachments pulled out."},{"time":223993,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":225887,"text":"They use these formidable devices\nlike scoops,"},{"time":230057,"text":"to remove the sperm from previous males\nthat the female has mated with."},{"time":234818,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":236909,"text":"So, what can we learn from this?"},{"time":239630,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":245333,"text":"All right, it is not a lesson in the sense\nof us imitating them"},{"time":250367,"text":"or of them setting\nan example for us to follow."},{"time":253915,"text":"Which, given this,\nis probably just as well."},{"time":257265,"text":"And also, did I mention sexual cannibalism\nis rampant among insects?"},{"time":260863,"text":"So, no, that's not the point."},{"time":263215,"text":"But what I think insects do,"},{"time":264976,"text":"is break a lot of the rules\nthat we humans have about the sex roles."},{"time":271319,"text":"So, people have this idea that nature\ndictates kind of a 1950s sitcom version"},{"time":276872,"text":"of what males and females are like."},{"time":278851,"text":"So that males are always\nsupposed to be dominant and aggressive,"},{"time":282028,"text":"and females are passive and coy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283794,"text":"But that's just not the case."},{"time":286606,"text":"So for example, take katydids,"},{"time":288692,"text":"which are relatives of crickets\nand grasshoppers."},{"time":291558,"text":"The males are very picky\nabout who they mate with,"},{"time":295059,"text":"because they not only transfer\nsperm during mating,"},{"time":298308,"text":"they also give the female\nsomething called a nuptial gift."},{"time":302798,"text":"You can see two katydids\nmating in these photos."},{"time":306499,"text":"In both panels,\nthe male's the one on the right,"},{"time":308843,"text":"and that sword-like appendage\nis the female's egg-laying organ."},{"time":313126,"text":"The white blob is the sperm,"},{"time":315677,"text":"the green blob is the nuptial gift,"},{"time":319087,"text":"and the male manufactures\nthis from his own body"},{"time":322477,"text":"and it's extremely costly to produce."},{"time":324679,"text":"It can weigh up to a third\nof his body mass."},{"time":327985,"text":"I will now pause for a moment\nand let you think about"},{"time":330543,"text":"what it would be like if human men,\nevery time they had sex,"},{"time":334730,"text":"had to produce something\nthat weighed 50, 60, 70 pounds."},{"time":340801,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":344432,"text":"Okay, they would not be able\nto do that very often."},{"time":347695,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":349216,"text":"And indeed, neither can the katydids."},{"time":352343,"text":"And so what that means"},{"time":354279,"text":"is the katydid males are very choosy"},{"time":358111,"text":"about who they offer\nthese nuptial gifts to."},{"time":361215,"text":"Now, the gift is very nutritious,"},{"time":363165,"text":"and the female eats it\nduring and after mating."},{"time":365883,"text":"So, the bigger it is,\nthe better off the male is,"},{"time":368264,"text":"because that means more time for his sperm"},{"time":370464,"text":"to drain into her body\nand fertilize her eggs."},{"time":373521,"text":"But it also means that the males\nare very passive about mating,"},{"time":377895,"text":"whereas the females\nare extremely aggressive and competitive,"},{"time":381444,"text":"in an attempt to get as many of these\nnutritious nuptial gifts as they can."},{"time":385784,"text":"So, it's not exactly\na stereotypical set of rules."},{"time":390974,"text":"Even more generally though,"},{"time":392709,"text":"males are actually not all that important\nin the lives of a lot of insects."},{"time":397797,"text":"In the social insects --\nthe bees and wasps and ants --"},{"time":402250,"text":"the individuals that you see every day --"},{"time":404869,"text":"the ants going back and forth\nto your sugar bowl,"},{"time":407338,"text":"the honey bees that are flitting\nfrom flower to flower --"},{"time":410371,"text":"all of those are always female."},{"time":413300,"text":"People have had a hard time getting\ntheir head around that idea for millennia."},{"time":417900,"text":"The ancient Greeks knew that there was\na class of bees, the drones,"},{"time":423022,"text":"that are larger than the workers,"},{"time":425097,"text":"although they disapproved\nof the drones' laziness"},{"time":427691,"text":"because they could see that\nthe drones just hang around the hive"},{"time":430770,"text":"until the mating flight --"},{"time":432319,"text":"they're the males."},{"time":433562,"text":"They hang around until the mating flight,"},{"time":435605,"text":"but they don't participate\nin gathering nectar or pollen."},{"time":438368,"text":"The Greeks couldn't figure out\nthe drones' sex,"},{"time":440676,"text":"and part of the confusion was that they\nwere aware of the stinging ability of bees"},{"time":445267,"text":"but they found it difficult to believe"},{"time":448148,"text":"that any animals that bore such a weapon\ncould possibly be a female."},{"time":451705,"text":"Aristotle tried to get involved as well."},{"time":454739,"text":"He suggested, \"OK, if the stinging\nindividuals are going to be the males ...\""},{"time":459351,"text":"Then he got confused,\nbecause that would have meant"},{"time":461841,"text":"the males were also taking care\nof the young in a colony,"},{"time":464594,"text":"and he seemed to think\nthat would be completely impossible."},{"time":469026,"text":"He then concluded that maybe\nbees had the organs of both sexes"},{"time":472099,"text":"in the same individual,"},{"time":473274,"text":"which is not that far-fetched,\nsome animals do that,"},{"time":475867,"text":"but he never really\ndid get it figured out."},{"time":478744,"text":"And you know, even today,\nmy students, for instance,"},{"time":482554,"text":"call every animal they see,\nincluding insects, a male."},{"time":487585,"text":"And when I tell them\nthat the ferocious army-ant soldiers"},{"time":491145,"text":"with their giant jaws,\nused to defend the colony,"},{"time":494102,"text":"are all always female,"},{"time":497228,"text":"they seem to not quite believe me."},{"time":499586,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":500755,"text":"And certainly all of the movies --\nAntz, Bee Movie --"},{"time":505979,"text":"portray the main character\nin the social insects as being male."},{"time":512869,"text":"Well, what difference does this make?"},{"time":514697,"text":"These are movies. They're fiction."},{"time":516358,"text":"They have talking animals in them."},{"time":518004,"text":"What difference does it make\nif they talk like Jerry Seinfeld?"},{"time":521708,"text":"I think it does matter,"},{"time":523896,"text":"and it's a problem that actually\nis part of a much deeper one"},{"time":526784,"text":"that has implications\nfor medicine and health"},{"time":530937,"text":"and a lot of other aspects of our lives."},{"time":533595,"text":"You all know that scientists\nuse what we call model systems,"},{"time":537112,"text":"which are creatures --\nwhite rats or fruit flies --"},{"time":540497,"text":"that are kind of stand-ins\nfor all other animals, including people."},{"time":545075,"text":"And the idea is\nthat what's true for a person"},{"time":548043,"text":"will also be true for the white rat."},{"time":550478,"text":"And by and large,\nthat turns out to be the case."},{"time":553482,"text":"But you can take the idea\nof a model system too far."},{"time":557924,"text":"And what I think we've done,"},{"time":560217,"text":"is use males, in any species,\nas though they are the model system."},{"time":565692,"text":"The norm."},{"time":566939,"text":"The way things are supposed to be."},{"time":569510,"text":"And females as a kind of variant --"},{"time":572583,"text":"something special that you only study\nafter you get the basics down."},{"time":577802,"text":"And so, back to the insects."},{"time":580509,"text":"I think what that means"},{"time":581881,"text":"is that people just couldn't see\nwhat was in front of them."},{"time":584724,"text":"Because they assumed that the world's\nstage was largely occupied by male players"},{"time":591184,"text":"and females would only have\nminor, walk-on roles."},{"time":595626,"text":"But when we do that, we really miss out\non a lot of what nature is like."},{"time":601588,"text":"And we can also miss out on the way\nnatural, living things, including people,"},{"time":608611,"text":"can vary."},{"time":610025,"text":"And I think that's why we've used males\nas models in a lot of medical research,"},{"time":615124,"text":"something that we know now to be a problem"},{"time":617213,"text":"if we want the results to apply\nto both men and women."},{"time":622760,"text":"Well, the last thing\nI really love about insects"},{"time":625311,"text":"is something that a lot of people\nfind unnerving about them."},{"time":628596,"text":"They have little, tiny brains"},{"time":630387,"text":"with very little cognitive ability,\nthe way we normally think of it."},{"time":634398,"text":"They have complicated behavior,\nbut they lack complicated brains."},{"time":639860,"text":"And so, we can't just think of them\nas though they're little people"},{"time":645061,"text":"because they don't do things\nthe way that we do."},{"time":648630,"text":"I really love that it's difficult\nto anthropomorphize insects,"},{"time":652754,"text":"to look at them and just think of them\nlike they're little people"},{"time":656301,"text":"in exoskeletons, with six legs."},{"time":658927,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":660212,"text":"Instead, you really have to accept them\non their own terms,"},{"time":663781,"text":"because insects make us question\nwhat's normal and what's natural."},{"time":669527,"text":"Now, you know, people write fiction\nand talk about parallel universes."},{"time":674184,"text":"They speculate about the supernatural,"},{"time":677506,"text":"maybe the spirits of the departed\nwalking among us."},{"time":682537,"text":"The allure of another world"},{"time":685757,"text":"is something that people say is part of\nwhy they want to dabble in the paranormal."},{"time":692376,"text":"But as far as I'm concerned,"},{"time":694689,"text":"who needs to be able to see dead people,"},{"time":696882,"text":"when you can see live insects?"},{"time":699262,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":700448,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}